resource "aws_instance" "example" {
  for_each = {
    "vm1" = "t2.micro"
    "vm2" = "t2.small"
  }

  ami           = "ami-123456"
  instance_type = each.value
}

output "instance_ids" {
  value = aws_instance.example[*].id
}

for_each creates two instances: vm1 and vm2.
The expression aws_instance.example[*].id is a splat expression that collects the id of each instance into a list.
The result is a list of instance IDs.

example:

resource "aws_instance" "example" {
  count = 3
  ami           = "ami-123456"
  instance_type = "t2.micro"
}

output "instance_ids" {
  value = aws_instance.example[*].id
}
the output will look something like:

[
  "i-abc123",
  "i-def456",
  "i-ghi789"
]

When you use for_each to create multiple instances of a resource in Terraform, you can reference all of them using a splat expression (*). This returns a list of values from the resource instances.
resource "aws_instance" "web" {
  for_each = {
    "one"   = "t2.micro"
    "two"   = "t2.small"
  }

  instance_type = each.value
  ami           = "ami-123456"
}

output "instance_ids" {
  value = aws_instance.web[*].id
}
